	it's not a 100% sure-fire indication of a pick-place file.

2007-12-31   Stuart Brorson * sdb AT cloud9 dot net *

	* ChangeLog, src/drill.c, src/drill.h, src/gerber.c, src/gerber.h,
	src/gerbv.c, src/pick-and-place.c, src/pick-and-place.h: Overhauled
	checks for file type.  Now all file types (Gerber, drill,
	pick-place) are FALSE by default, and only are TRUE when positive of
	file type indications are found.  Also added specific check for
	RS-284-D, and throw error if -D is found.

